        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-22T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="1333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.7146/3–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-23T12:00:00+08:00">March 23, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 23—1:58 a.
                        m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>462. ReContel 444, March 21. Requested information was handed inspector 1100
                    hours today under cover unaddressed memo signed by <pb facs="1083" n="1073" xml:id="pg_1073"/> me as Consul General. As regards radio station, it was
                    confirmed Consulate General possessed one “which was of course established
                    according to a pertinent agreement”.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking, Shanghai and Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
